 {"id":"frankenpandas-0yz7","title":"[REALITY-CHECK HIGH] MultiIndex marked Yes-foundation but row MultiIndex absent","description":"README capability table: MultiIndex Yes (foundation) — note the foundation qualifier. Reality: br-r4au tried to ship row MultiIndex emission for grouped rolling/resample by encoding tuples as flat Utf8 strings (a, 2024-01) because real row MultiIndex is not wired through DataFrame; br-ch4o reverted that workaround back to group-key column + bucket-only flat index. Concrete absences: (1) DataFrame::index returns Index<IndexLabel> not MultiIndex<Vec<IndexLabel>>; (2) groupby([k1,k2]).sum output uses string-flattened keys like s:a|i:1 (per FP-P2C-005, FP-P2C-011) not real (k1, k2) tuples; (3) no .loc[(a, 1)] tuple-key indexing; (4) stack/unstack and reset_index for MultiIndex frames are scaffolded but not behaviorally complete. Suggested: split the README MultiIndex row into Column MultiIndex (Yes-foundation) and Row MultiIndex (No), file an epic for genuine row MultiIndex.","notes":"cc-pandas triage 2026-04-22 (commit 14a74c6): split the conflated 'MultiIndex | Yes (foundation)' capability table row into Row MultiIndex (Scaffolded) and Column MultiIndex (Yes-foundation), matching the actual in-tree reality after br-ch4o reverted br-r4au's tuple-emission attempt. MultiIndex section prose (README.md:396) now names the flattening mechanism ('a|1' separator via set_index_multi) and enumerates the specific scaffolded surfaces (tuple .loc, row-MultiIndex groupby output, stack/unstack, reset_index round-trip) with cross-references to the capability table and Limitations. Existing Limitations entry (README.md:1372) already honest; kept. Follow-up epic filed as br-frankenpandas-1zzp covering the full row-axis integration work (6 slices: DataFrame row-axis type, multi-key GroupBy output, tuple indexing, reshape round-trips, IO multi-row index block, live-oracle coverage).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc-pandas","c